Removed old console.log wrappers

Remove the trace function and the file common.js

Our old trace() utility fun ction only added timestamps to logs, but prevented modern use of console.log. It also made it hard to quickly find the line where the call was made, since it always tracked back to common.js.

This change removes the function and changes all calls to trace to console.log instead. We'll loose the timestamp in the logs, but I believe this is more valuable as we now can properly log objects in the console as well as find the source of each call more easily.

AppRTC new signaling model.

Updates AppRTC GAE server and web client to use the new signaling model.

Clients are required to register with GAE before sending messages, and will
receive a client id upon registration. The first client C1 sends all its
signaling messages to GAE. GAE will store the messages if the second client C2
has not registered yet, otherwise GAE will forward the messages to Collider,
which will then deliver the message over C2's websocket connection. When C2
registers it will receive all stored messages from C1. C2 sends all its
signaling messages through Collider. Each GAE registration is matched
with a BYE command to GAE on hangup.
